  "doc_id": "59831",
  "text": "ITSPOKE is an ITS which uses spoken dialogue for the purpose of providing spoken feedback and correcting misconceptions [CITATION_1] . The student and the system interact with each other in English to discus the student's answers. ITSPOKE uses a microphone as an input device for the student's speech and sends the signal to the Sphinx2 recognizer [CITATION_2] . Litman et al. showed that ITSPOKE is more effective than typed dialogue; however, there was no evidence that ITSPOKE increases student learning [CITATION_3] . In addition, it was clear that speech recognition errors did not decrease learning.",
